<body>

  <!-- ── Header ── -->
  <header>
    <h1>🌳 Fractal Tree Explorer</h1>
    <p>Visualise recursion depth, branch growth, and stack behaviour in real time</p>
  </header>

  <!-- ── Controls ── -->
  <div class="controls">
    <div class="control-group">
      <label>Recursion Depth</label>
      <div class="slider-row">
        <input type="range" id="depthSlider" min="1" max="12" value="7" />
        <div class="badge" id="depthBadge">7</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-row">
      <div class="stat">Branches: <span id="statBranches">–</span></div>
      <div class="stat">Max frames: <span id="statFrames">–</span></div>
      <div class="stat">Draw time: <span id="statTime">–</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Warning banner ── -->
  <div class="warning-banner" id="warningBanner">
    <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#f0883e" stroke-width="2">
      <path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 001.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 001.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 00-3.42 0z"/>
      <line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/>
    </svg>
    <span id="warningText"></span>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Canvas ── -->
  <div class="canvas-wrapper">
    <canvas id="treeCanvas" width="780" height="520"></canvas>
    <div class="canvas-label">fractal-tree.html</div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Explanation cards ── -->
  <section class="explanation">

    <!-- Card 1 – Recursion depth -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2><span class="icon">🔁</span> What is Recursion Depth?</h2>
      <p>
        Every time a function calls itself, the JavaScript engine pushes a new
        <strong>stack frame</strong> onto the call stack. The recursion depth is
        simply how many frames are stacked at the deepest point of execution.
      </p>
      <p>
        In this fractal tree each branch spawns two child branches. At depth
        <em>d</em> the tree contains <strong>2<sup>d+1</sup> − 1</strong> total
        branches. The table below shows how quickly that grows:
      </p>

      <!-- Depth meter -->
      <div class="depth-meter" id="depthMeter"></div>

      <div style="margin-top:14px; overflow-x:auto;">
        <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:0.82rem;">
          <thead>
            <tr style="color:#58a6ff;text-align:left;">
              <th style="padding:6px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #30363d;">Depth</th>
              <th style="padding:6px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #30363d;">Total Branches</th>
              <th style="padding:6px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #30363d;">Max Stack Frames</th>
              <th style="padding:6px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #30363d;">Risk</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody id="depthTable"></tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Card 2 – Stack overflow -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2><span class="icon">💥</span> Stack Overflow Risks</h2>
      <p>
        Each JavaScript engine allocates a fixed amount of memory for the call
        stack — typically enough for <strong>10,000 – 15,000</strong> frames in
        V8 (Chrome/Node) and slightly less in SpiderMonkey (Firefox). When a
        recursive function exceeds that limit the engine throws a
        <code style="color:#ff7b72;">RangeError: Maximum call stack size exceeded</code>.
      </p>
      <ul style="margin-top:10px;">
        <li><strong>Unbounded recursion</strong> — a missing or incorrect base case causes infinite recursion and an immediate crash.</li>
        <li><strong>Deep mutual recursion</strong> — function A calls B which calls A; the depth accumulates from both sides.</li>
        <li><strong>Large input data</strong> — processing a deeply nested JSON tree or a long linked list recursively can silently overflow in production.</li>
        <li><strong>Closures capturing large state</strong> — each frame may hold references that prevent garbage collection, compounding memory pressure.</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top:10px;">
        For this tree, depth 12 requires only 12 frames at any one time (the
        engine unwinds each branch before exploring the next), so it is safe —
        but the <strong>2<sup>13</sup> − 1 = 8 191</strong> total draw calls
        make rendering noticeably slow, demonstrating a different kind of
        performance ceiling.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Card 3 – Solutions -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2><span class="icon">🛠️</span> Practical Solutions</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Iterative conversion with an explicit stack</strong> — replace
          the call stack with a plain array acting as a stack. This is the most
          general solution and eliminates overflow risk entirely.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Tail-call optimisation (TCO)</strong> — rewrite the function
          so the recursive call is the very last operation. The engine can then
          reuse the current frame. TCO is mandated by ES2015 but only Safari
          implements it fully; V8 removed its implementation.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Trampolining</strong> — instead of calling itself directly, the
          function returns a thunk (a zero-argument function). A trampoline loop
          keeps calling the returned thunk until a plain value emerges, keeping
          the stack depth at 1.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Memoisation / dynamic programming</strong> — for problems with
          overlapping sub-problems (e.g. Fibonacci), cache results to avoid
          recomputing — and re-entering — the same recursive paths.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Depth limiting with a guard</strong> — the simplest safeguard:
          add a <code style="color:#79c0ff;">if (depth &lt;= 0) return;</code>
          base case and enforce a maximum depth at the call site.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <!-- Iterative code example -->
      <div class="code-block">
        <pre><span class="cm">// Iterative fractal tree using an explicit stack array</span>
<span class="cm">// — no call-stack frames consumed by recursion at all.</span>
<span class="kw">function</span> <span class="fn">drawTreeIterative</span>(ctx, startX, startY, angle, length, depth) {
  <span class="cm">// Each item represents one "branch task"</span>
  <span class="kw">const</span> <span class="nm">stack</span> = [{ startX, startY, angle, length, depth }];

  <span class="kw">while</span> (<span class="nm">stack</span>.length <span class="op">></span> <span class="nm">0</span>) {
    <span class="kw">const</span> { startX, startY, angle, length, depth } = <span class="nm">stack</span>.<span class="fn">pop</span>();

    <span class="kw">if</span> (depth <span class="op">===</span> <span class="nm">0</span>) <span class="kw">continue</span>;   <span class="cm">// base case</span>

    <span class="kw">const</span> endX = startX <span class="op">+</span> length <span class="op">*</span> Math.<span class="fn">cos</span>(angle);
    <span class="kw">const</span> endY = startY <span class="op">-</span> length <span class="op">*</span> Math.<span class="fn">sin</span>(angle);

    ctx.<span class="fn">beginPath</span>();
    ctx.<span class="fn">moveTo</span>(startX, startY);
    ctx.<span class="fn">lineTo</span>(endX, endY);
    ctx.<span class="fn">stroke</span>();

    <span class="cm">// Push child branches — right then left</span>
    <span class="nm">stack</span>.<span class="fn">push</span>({ startX: endX, startY: endY,
                  angle: angle <span class="op">-</span> Math.PI / <span class="nm">5</span>,
                  length: length <span class="op">*</span> <span class="nm">0.72</span>, depth: depth <span class="op">-</span> <span class="nm">1</span> });
    <span class="nm">stack</span>.<span class="fn">push</span>({ startX: endX, startY: endY,
                  angle: angle <span class="op">+</span> Math.PI / <span class="nm">5</span>,
                  length: length <span class="op">*</span> <span class="nm">0.72</span>, depth: depth <span class="op">-</span> <span class="nm">1</span> });
  }
}</pre>
      </div>

      <!-- Trampoline code example -->
      <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:10px;">
        <pre><span class="cm">// Trampoline pattern — keeps the real call stack at depth 1.</span>
<span class="kw">const</span> <span class="fn">trampoline</span> = fn <span class="op">=></span> (...args) <span class="op">=></span> {
  <span class="kw">let</span> result = fn(...args);
  <span class="kw">while</span> (<span class="kw">typeof</span> result <span class="op">===</span> <span class="st">'function'</span>) result = result();
  <span class="kw">return</span> result;
};

<span class="cm">// Recursive factorial rewritten for trampolining</span>
<span class="kw">const</span> <span class="fn">factHelper</span> = (n, acc <span class="op">=</span> <span class="nm">1</span>) <span class="op">=></span>
  n <span class="op"><=</span> <span class="nm">1</span> ? acc : () <span class="op">=></span> <span class="fn">factHelper</span>(n <span class="op">-</span> <span class="nm">1</span>, n <span class="op">*</span> acc);

<span class="kw">const</span> <span class="fn">factorial</span> = <span class="fn">trampoline</span>(factHelper);
<span class="fn">factorial</span>(<span class="nm">100000</span>); <span class="cm">// never overflows</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Card 4 – How the tree is drawn -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2><span class="icon">🎨</span> How the Recursive Tree is Drawn</h2>
      <p>
        The recursive <code style="color:#d2a8ff;">drawBranch</code> function
        below is what this demo actually uses. Each call draws one line segment
        and then calls itself twice — once angled left and once angled right —
        with a shorter length and decremented depth. When depth reaches zero the
        function returns immediately (the base case).
      </p>
      <div class="code-block">
        <pre><span class="kw">function</span> <span class="fn">drawBranch</span>(ctx, x, y, angle, length, depth, maxDepth) {
  <span class="kw">if</span> (depth <span class="op">===</span> <span class="nm">0</span>) <span class="kw">return</span>;   <span class="cm">// ← base case prevents infinite recursion</span>

  <span class="kw">const</span> endX = x <span class="op">+</span> length <span class="op">*</span> Math.<span class="fn">cos</span>(angle);
  <span class="kw">const</span> endY = y <span class="op">-</span> length <span class="op">*</span> Math.<span class="fn">sin</span>(angle);

  <span class="cm">// Visual styling based on depth</span>
  <span class="kw">const</span> t = depth / maxDepth;
  ctx.lineWidth   = <span class="nm">1</span> <span class="op">+</span> t <span class="op">*</span> <span class="nm">7</span>;
  ctx.strokeStyle = <span class="fn">branchColour</span>(t);

  ctx.<span class="fn">beginPath</span>();
  ctx.<span class="fn">moveTo</span>(x, y);
  ctx.<span class="fn">lineTo</span>(endX, endY);
  ctx.<span class="fn">stroke</span>();

  <span class="cm">// Two recursive calls — left branch and right branch</span>
  <span class="fn">drawBranch</span>(ctx, endX, endY, angle <span class="op">+</span> ANGLE_SPREAD,
             length <span class="op">*</span> LENGTH_RATIO, depth <span class="op">-</span> <span class="nm">1</span>, maxDepth);
  <span class="fn">drawBranch</span>(ctx, endX, endY, angle <span class="op">-</span> ANGLE_SPREAD,
             length <span class="op">*</span> LENGTH_RATIO, depth <span class="op">-</span> <span class="nm">1</span>, maxDepth);
}</pre>
      </div>
    </div>

  </section>

  <script>
    /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       Constants
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
    const ANGLE_SPREAD  = Math.PI / 5;   // 36 degrees
    const LENGTH_RATIO  = 0.72;
    const TRUNK_LENGTH  = 110;

    /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       DOM references
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
    const slider        = document.getElementById('depthSlider');
    const badge         = document.getElementById('depthBadge');
    const canvas        = document.getElementById('treeCanvas');
    const ctx           = canvas.getContext('2d');
    const statBranches  = document.getElementById('statBranches');
    const statFrames    = document.getElementById('statFrames');
    const statTime      = document.getElementById('statTime');
    const warningBanner = document.getElementById('warningBanner');
    const warningText   = document.getElementById('warningText');
    const depthMeter    = document.getElementById('depthMeter');
    const depthTableEl  = document.getElementById('depthTable');

    /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       Colour helpers
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
    function lerpColour(t) {
      // t = 1 (trunk) → warm brown, t = 0 (leaf) → bright green/yellow
      const r = Math.round(139 + (80  - 139) * (1 - t));
      const g = Math.round( 90 + (200 -  90) * (1 - t));
      const b = Math.round( 43 + ( 60 -  43) * (1 - t));
      return `rgb(${r},${g},${b})`;
    }

    function depthCellColour(d) {
      const colours = [
        '#238636','#2ea043','#3fb950',
        '#56d364','#7ee787','#a5f3a5',
        '#f0883e','#e3b341','#d29922',
        '#bc8cff','#a371f7','#ff7b72'
      ];
      return colours[d - 1] || '#58a6ff';
    }

    function riskLabel(d) {
      if (d <= 6)  return { text: 'Safe',     colour: '#3fb950' };
      if (d <= 9)  return { text: 'Moderate', colour: '#e3b341' };
      if (d <= 11) return { text: 'High',     colour: '#f0883e' };
      return               { text: 'Very High',colour: '#ff7b72' };
    }

    /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       Populate static depth table & meter
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
    function buildStaticUI() {
      // Depth meter cells
      depthMeter.innerHTML = '';
      for (let d = 1; d <= 12; d++) {
        const cell = document.createElement('div');
        cell.className = 'depth-cell';
        cell.id = `cell-${d}`;
        cell.style.background = depthCellColour(d);
        cell.textContent = d;
        depthMeter.appendChild(cell);
      }

      // Depth table rows
      depthTableEl.innerHTML = '';
      for (let d = 1; d <= 12; d++) {
        const branches = Math.pow(2, d + 1) - 1;
        const maxFrames = d;
        const risk = riskLabel(d);
        const tr = document.createElement('tr');
        tr.id = `row-${d}`;
        tr.style.transition = 'background 0.3s';
        tr.innerHTML = `
          <td style="padding:6px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #21262d;color:#e6edf3;">${d}</td>
          <td style="padding:6px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #21262d;">${branches.toLocaleString()}</td>
          <td style="padding:6px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #21262d;">${maxFrames}</td>
          <td style="padding:6px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #21262d;">
            <span style="color:${risk.colour};font-weight:600;">${risk.text}</span>
          </td>`;
        depthTableEl.appendChild(tr);
      }
    }

    /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       Highlight active depth in table & meter
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
    function highlightDepth(d) {
      for (let i = 1; i <= 12; i++) {
        const row  = document.getElementById(`row-${i}`);
        const cell = document.getElementById(`cell-${i}`);
        if (row)  row.style.background  = i === d ? '#21262d' : 'transparent';
        if (cell) cell.style.opacity    = i <= d  ? '1'       : '0.25';
      }
    }

    /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       Recursive draw function
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
    let branchCount = 0;

    function drawBranch(x, y, angle, length, depth, maxDepth) {
      if (depth === 0) return;

      branchCount++;

      const endX = x + length * Math.cos(angle);
      const endY = y - length * Math.sin(angle);

      const t = depth / maxDepth;
      ctx.lineWidth   = 1 + t * 7;
      ctx.strokeStyle = lerpColour(t);
      ctx.lineCap     = 'round';

      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(x, y);
      ctx.lineTo(endX, endY);
      ctx.stroke();

      drawBranch(endX, endY, angle + ANGLE_SPREAD, length * LENGTH_RATIO, depth - 1, maxDepth);
      drawBranch(endX, endY, angle - ANGLE_SPREAD, length * LENGTH_RATIO, depth - 1, maxDepth);
    }

    /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       Main render
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
    function render(depth) {
      const W = canvas.width;
      const H = canvas.height;

      // Clear with a subtle gradient sky
      const sky = ctx.createLinearGradient(0, 0, 0, H);
      sky.addColorStop(0, '#0d1117');
      sky.addColorStop(1, '#161b22');
      ctx.fillStyle = sky;
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);

      // Ground line
      ctx.strokeStyle = '#21262d';
      ctx.lineWidth = 1;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(0, H - 20);
      ctx.lineTo(W, H - 20);
      ctx.stroke();

      branchCount = 0;
      const t0 = performance.now();

      drawBranch(
        W / 2,           // start X (centre)
        H - 20,          // start Y (ground)
        Math.PI / 2,     // pointing straight up
        TRUNK_LENGTH,    // initial length
        depth,           // current depth
        depth            // max depth (for colour normalisation)
      );

      const elapsed = performance.now() - t0;

      // Update stats
      statBranches.textContent = branchCount.toLocaleString();
      statFrames.textContent   = depth;
      statTime.textContent     = elapsed.toFixed(2) + ' ms';

      // Warning banner
      const totalBranches = Math.pow(2, depth + 1) - 1;
      if (depth >= 11) {
        warningBanner.classList.add('visible');
        warningText.textContent =
          `Depth ${depth} renders ${totalBranches.toLocaleString()} branches ` +
          `(${elapsed.toFixed(1)} ms). At extreme depths consider the iterative ` +
          `approach shown below to avoid UI jank.`;
      } else {
