        variables, the return address, and parameters.  The call stack has a hard size
        limit set by the engine or OS (typically <strong>10 000 – 15 000 frames</strong>
        in V8/Node, fewer in some browsers).
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top:10px">
        When the limit is exceeded the engine throws a
        <code>RangeError: Maximum call stack size exceeded</code> — commonly called a
        <em>stack overflow</em>.  For this binary tree the call count explodes:
      </p>
