    <div class="card info">
      <h3><span class="icon">🔢</span> What Does "Recursion Depth" Mean?</h3>
      <p>
        Every time a function calls itself, the JavaScript engine pushes a new
        <strong>stack frame</strong> onto the <em>call stack</em> — a fixed-size
        region of memory that tracks active function calls.  The recursion depth
        is simply the maximum number of frames alive at the same moment, i.e. how
        many nested calls are open simultaneously.
      </p>
      <p>
