## What's inside

### 🌳 The Fractal Tree
| Feature | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Algorithm** | Classic recursive binary tree — each branch spawns a left and right child |
| **Depth slider** | 1 – 12 levels; canvas redraws on every `input` event |
| **Angle slider** | 10° – 60° spread between sibling branches |
| **Ratio slider** | 50 % – 85 % child-to-parent length ratio |
| **Colour** | Interpolates warm brown (trunk) → bright green (tips) |
| **Line width** | Proportional to depth so trunks are thick and tips are hair-thin |
| **Responsive** | Canvas resizes with the viewport |

### 📚 The Explanation Cards
1. **What recursion depth means** — stack frames, base cases, annotated code
